Here's the full **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit of your `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests` class (MSTest, .NET 10, `[TestCategory("Integration")]`).

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High | 3 | 3 |
| Medium | 1 | 1 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **4** |

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Sleepy Test

**Smell:** Sleepy Test (testsmells.org #3)
**Method:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 82–90)
**Integration calibration:** Even for integration tests, `Thread.Sleep` introduces non-determinism and inflates suite runtime. Downgraded severity is not warranted here because a polling/event-driven alternative exists.

```csharp
// ❌ Current
Thread.Sleep(3000);
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

**Fix — use a polling helper or async wait:**

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
var cts = new CancellationTokenSource(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5));
while (!_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
    await Task.Delay(100, cts.Token);

Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Flaky CI failures on slow machines; 3 s of wasted wall-clock time per run regardless of actual notification speed.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**Smell:** Conditional Test Logic (testsmells.org #1)
**Method:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (lines 94–109)

```csharp
// ❌ Current
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

Only one branch ever executes. The other is dead code masquerading as coverage.

**Fix — assert the expected type explicitly:**

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<User>(loaded);  // or PremiumUser if that's what Insert creates
Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
```

If both paths are needed, write **two separate tests** — one per scenario.

**Risk if unfixed:** Hidden testing gap; test passes regardless of which branch runs.

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Smell:** Unknown Test / Empty Test (testsmells.org #4)
**Method:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (lines 113–119)

```csharp
// ❌ Current — no assertion, counts as "pass" if no exception
for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
{
    _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
}
```

**Fix — verify the post-condition:**

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed
for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));

Assert.AreEqual(100, _repository.ListAll().Count);
```

**Risk if unfixed:** False confidence — silently broken inserts still produce a green test.

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**Smell:** Assertion Roulette (extended catalog)
**Method:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (lines 28–39)

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

Four assertions, none with a message parameter. A failure reports only "Assert.AreEqual failed" with no context.

**Fix — add messages to disambiguate:**

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should exist after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Id should be assigned by the database");
```

**Integration calibration:** Severity stays Medium (not downgraded) — message-less assertion roulette affects any test scope equally.

**Risk if unfixed:** Longer debugging when a build goes red; the MSTest runner won't tell you *which* property mismatched.

---

## Smell-Free Patterns ✅

The following tests are well-structured — clear Arrange/Act/Assert, focused scope, meaningful assertions:

- `UpdateUser_ModifiesExistingRecord` — single concern, clear assertion.
- `DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase` — clean negative assertion.
- `ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted` — `AreEqual(3, …)` is self-documenting (3 items just inserted). No Magic Number smell.
- `InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity` — async workflow with proper assertion; acceptable use of `Task.Run` for concurrency testing.

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add `Assert.AreEqual(100, …)` | ~1 min |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into two typed tests | ~5 min |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with polling loop | ~10 min |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | Add message params to assertions | ~3 min |

**Overall verdict:** 4 of 8 tests carry smells — the core CRUD tests are solid, but the secondary tests need attention. Fixing priorities 1–3 removes all High-severity findings and directly reduces flakiness risk.
